## Design Decisions

### Checkmark Icon (✓)
- Universal success symbol
- Green and bold for emphasis
- Consistent with error (✗) and other indicators

### Simple Line Format
- No panel needed (these are quick confirmations)
- Single line is sufficient for success
- Errors get panels for more information

### Key Index Highlighting
- Amber color makes key number pop
- Essential when setting multiple keys in sequence
- Consistent with button events display

### Color Preview
- When filling with a color, show it in that color if possible
- Adds visual confirmation that color was understood
- Falls back to regular value styling if color parsing fails

### Filename Display
- Show just filename, not full path (cleaner)
- Fall back to full path if filename extraction fails
- Quoted or styled to distinguish from surrounding text

## Multiple Key Operations
When setting multiple keys (future batch operation), these can be called in sequence:
```
  ✓ Key 0 set to icon1.png
  ✓ Key 1 set to icon2.png
  ✓ Key 2 set to icon3.png
```

