## Implementation

### Enhanced error Method
```rust
fn error(&self, error: &SdError) {
    let mut content = Text::new("");
    content.append("\n");

    // Error icon and message
    content.append_styled("  ✗ ", Style::new().bold().color(self.theme.error.clone()));
    content.append_styled(&error.to_string(), Style::new().bold());
    content.append("\n");

    // Special handling for MultipleDevices error
    if let SdError::MultipleDevices { serials } = error {
        content.append("\n");
        content.append_styled("  Available devices:\n", self.theme.label.clone());
        for serial in serials {
            content.append_styled(&format!("    • {}\n", serial), 
                self.theme.device_serial.clone());
        }
    }

    // Suggestion section
    if let Some(suggestion) = error.suggestion() {
        content.append("\n");
        content.append_styled("  Suggestion:\n", self.theme.label.clone());
        content.append_styled(&format!("  {}\n", suggestion), 
            self.theme.muted.clone());
    }

    content.append("\n");

    let panel = Panel::from_rich_text(content, self.width().saturating_sub(4))
        .title("Error")
        .border_style(Style::new().color(self.theme.error.clone()))
        .rounded();

    self.console.print_renderable(&panel);
}
```

## Design Decisions

### Red Border, Not Background
- Red background can be overwhelming and hard to read
- Red border draws attention without impairing readability
- White/default text on terminal background stays readable

### Error Icon (✗)
- Unicode multiply sign is universally understood
- Bold and colored for emphasis
- Consistent with success checkmark (✓)

### Suggestion Section
- Separated visually from error message
- Muted color indicates it's supplementary info
- Actionable: tells user what to DO, not just what's wrong

### Special Cases
- MultipleDevices gets list of serials (actionable information)
- Other errors can have custom handling added similarly
- Pattern match on SdError variants for special formatting

### Panel Title
- Simple "Error" title (not the error type)
- Error details are in the body
- Keeps title short and scannable

## Error Types and Their Display

| Error | Display | Suggestion |
|-------|---------|------------|
| NoDevicesFound | "No Stream Deck devices found" | "Ensure Stream Deck is connected via USB" |
| MultipleDevices | "Multiple devices found" + list | "Use --serial to specify which device" |
| DeviceNotFound | "Device 'XXX' not found" | "Check serial with 'sd list'" |
| InvalidKeyIndex | "Invalid key 32" | "Use key index 0-31" |
| InvalidBrightness | "Invalid brightness 150" | "Use value between 0 and 100" |
| ImageNotFound | "Image file not found" | "Check path exists" |

